social_posts.post_text: Been offline for awhile working on my mental health, my relationships, renovating the business, & reimagining life, quite frankly. But here’s a cute pic from last week of Babes and I at a fundraiser. First time I got him in a bow tie so that’s a win. 🤙🏻

When friends feel like family.💫
Grateful to do life with these two.
Carving mountains with my ride or die. 🖤
Sweets and treats with the crew. Won’t tell you how much money we all spent trying to win stuffed animals we didn’t even want. 🥹

I love learning about Love with you.♡

“Love is patient, love is kind. It does not envy, it does not boast, it is not proud. It does not dishonor others, it is not self-seeking, it is not easily angered, it keeps no record of wrongs. Love does not delight in deceit but rejoices with the truth. Love always protects, always trusts, always hopes, always perseveres.
Love never fails.”
1 Corinthians 13:4-8

Dear Grandmother, 
I have loved spending time with you this month. Your heart for God is inspiring. Your devotion to God’s Word is encouraging. Your love for your family is so felt. Your contentment with Life is enlightening. Christ in you is so palpable. Your faithfulness to God’s miracle is a story worth honoring. Your legacy for serving God with your life is a legacy that I believe will last forever. I have enjoyed being in your presence and toting you around to see all the things. Ninety-three years young and still going strong. I feel so grateful to have you as my grandmother. Thanks for coming to visit. I love you.
-L

To love is it’s own reward. ♡
Summertime in Laguna.

Grateful… Because I know an angel has been watching over me my entire life, my Mom. I am so grateful for the time spent the past couple of weeks… beaching, hiking, paddle boarding, and road trip’n. Your positive attitude, passion for life, heart of gratitude, and love for God inspires me. I love you!

Barefoot is the new normal. 👣
Officially converted Chase to the van life. 

After a couple years of persuasion I’ve officially converted chase to van loving and living. We have done plenty of micro adventures (2-3 day trips) together and he was sold. I did a 40 day solo trip this spring in the van and of course loved it… but adding another person might be another story. We left for our first long-range van trip this week. 18 days traveling in the van together; working and playing. Considering my van is one of the smallest sprinter vans on the market and chase is one of the tallest men not on the market… we’ll let you know in 3 weeks if we recommend this type of travel together or not. Either way, should be an adventure. Might post some more trip pics, might not. Just grateful to be on the road again and to have my partner in crime with me this go around.

Recap of our time in the John Muir Wilderness.
3 days offline. 17 mile loop hike. 9 glacial lakes. 2 peaks. 5 waterfalls. 2 cold plunges, and a 2 night stay under the stars. Grateful to take some time away from the busyness of life and learning to slow down and connect with the rhythms of nature. 
Next stop Mammoth Lakes.

Grateful. ♡
